  "text": "Transmural endoscopic drainage is a common method of treatment for patients with symptomatic WOPN [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Single transluminal gateway technique (SGT) is based on the complete removal of necrotic tissues through a single fistula created between the cavity of necrotic collection and the lumen of the gastrointestinal tract (stomach or duodenum) [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The described technique is particularly efficient in the case of unilocular necrotic collections. WOPN in most of the patients takes the form of a multilocular space divided by septa.",
